com.storytron.uber

Class Prop

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.storytron.uber.Word
      • com.storytron.uber.Prop
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<Word>

    public final class Prop
extends Word
    This class represents storyworld things. The Prop state contains some attributes and most of the implementation just sets or gets them.

    A Prop has the traits

    • carried, visible, inPlay, owner, location, description. Which can be manipulated with getters and setters.
    • For each PropFloatTrait in the model (Deikto) it holds the value of the trait. The values can be manipulated through the methods getTrait(FloatTrait) and setTrait(FloatTrait, float).
    • For each Prop TextTrait in the model (Deikto) it holds the value of the trait. The values can be manipulated through the methods getText(TextTrait) and #setText(TextTrait, float).
    • For each Actor, it has a knowsMe value that tells if the actor knows the Prop. Manipulable through getKnowsMe(Actor) and setKnowsMe(Actor, boolean)
    • image: holds in memory an image associated to the Prop. Manipulated through the methods getImage(Deikto) and setImage(ScaledImage). It is also possible to retrieve the image as a sequence of png bytes (getImageJPGBytes(Deikto)). This is useful for sending the image through the cable. If the image is null the png bytes are obtained from the file on disk.
    • imageFilename: holds the path to an image file associated to the Stage. It is manipulated through the methods getImageName() and setImageName(String), but is also set to null when a null image is set using setImage(ScaledImage) (setImage(null)).
